 approach attests to his innovativeness and his halakhic moderation, as he tried to rule as leniently as possible on matters concerning non-Jews. In this book, R. Meir Simcha is shown to be a truly influential rabbi whose contributions will long be a source of study and discussion.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Apr 2020) 7aRELIGION / Judaism / General.2bisacsh1 aBasser, Herbert, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGotlieb, Meshulam08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertASP eBook Package 2016z978311068816040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781618114907423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781618114907.jpg  a978-3-11-068816-0  ASP eBook Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK